{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Xq8oqdLg9o6JoJHeC3fUEv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The controller is version 1.14.1. This version supports OpenTelemetry natively. I need to:\n\n1. Create the `otel-echo` backend service and deployment in the `demo` namespace\n2. Create an ingress for `otel.example.com` pointing to `otel-echo` on the `/otel-check` path\n3. Enable OpenTelemetry in the ingress-nginx controller configmap with:\n   - `enable-opentelemetry: \"true\"`\n   - `opentelemetry-collector-host: \"otel-collector.otel.svc\"`\n   - `opentelemetry-collector-port: \"4317\"`\n   - `otel-sampler: \"AlwaysOn\"` for 100% sampling\n   - `log-format-upstream` with the specified format\n\nThe task mentions the OpenTelemetry collector is already running at `otel-collector.otel.svc:4317`, so I should assume that namespace and service already exist rather than creating them myself.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":508,"cache_read_input_tokens":35484,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":508},"output_tokens":27,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bd487f94-0c3d-45b2-be20-9528aacb64d1","uuid":"e77da36f-c1ad-4da8-8309-cceaea0ab42e","request_id":"req_011Cc6iU7bdfPYkUVW4nwgUe"}
